tory: Jacques Chouinard from Beaumont-la-Ronce in Indre-et-Loire, France, married Louise Jean in Quebec City, QC, in 1692. His descendants also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Sweeney</i> and <i>Swe(e)nor</i>, and also the surname   Parent  ."]},{"name":"Parrent","meanings":["English: variant of   Parent  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice CARENT was born in 1404, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Clarent, was 26 and her mother, Margaret Stourton, was 30. She married John Westbury in 1434, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 29 March 1484, in Winfrith, Dorset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1404–29 MAR 1484":"1404–29. märts 1484","1404–1484":"1404–1484","1405–1484":"1405–1484","–Male":"Surnud","1421–1479":"1421–1479","1378–1476":"1378–1476","1374–1463":"1374–1463","1404":"1404","1479":"1479","1434":"1434","29 MAR 1484":"29. märts 1484","1378":"1378","1421":"1421","1476":"1476","8 April 1476":"8. aprill 1476","1463":"1463","1374":"1374","1484":"1484","1405":"1405","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Gisburn, Yorkshire,